Git Configuration
• git config --global user.name "Your Name": Set your name for commit attribution.
• git config --global user.email "youremail@example.com": Set your email for commit attribution.
• git config --global alias.<alias-name> <git-command>: Create an alias for a Git command.

Creating and Cloning Repositories
• git init: Initialize a new Git repository.
• git clone <repository-url>: Clone a remote repository onto your local machine.

Basic Operations
• git status: Show the status of the working directory and staging area.
• git add <file>: Add file changes to the staging area.
• git commit -m "Commit message": Create a new commit with the staged changes.
• git diff: Display the differences between files or commits.

Branching and Merging
• git branch: List all branches.
• git branch <branch-name>: Create a new branch.
• git branch -d <branch-name>: Delete a branch.
• git checkout <branch-name>: Switch to a different branch.
• git merge <branch-name>: Merge changes from one branch into the current branch.
• git rebase <branch-name>: Reapply commits on top of another branch.
• git cherry-pick <commit>: Apply a specific commit to the current branch.

Remote Repository Operations
• git remote add <remote-name> <repository-url>: Add a new remote repository.
• git remote -v: List all remote repositories.
• git push <remote-name> <branch-name>: Push local commits to a remote repository.
• git pull <remote-name> <branch-name>: Fetch changes from a remote repository and merge them into the current branch.

History and Commits
• git log: Show commit history.
• git log --oneline: Show a concise commit history.
• git show <commit>: Show information about a specific commit.
• git blame <file>: Display the author and commit details for each line in a file.

Undoing Changes
• git reset <commit>: Unstage changes or move the branch pointer.
• git revert <commit>: Create a new commit that undoes a previous commit.
• git stash: Temporarily save changes that are not ready to be committed.

Collaboration
• git fetch <remote-name>: Fetch changes from a remote repository.
• git push <remote-name> <branch-name>: Publish local changes to a remote repository.
• git pull <remote-name> <branch-name>: Fetch and merge changes from a remote repository.

Tags
• git tag: List all tags.
• git tag <tag-name> <commit>: Create a new tag for a specific commit.
• git tag -d <tag-name>: Delete a tag
